@Node HOW "How to edit items in the Config Program"

    You use the CONFIG program the same way you use CNet's VDE Editors by
first moving the highlighted block to the item you wish to edit, then you
press your ENTER/RETURN key.

    Some items are toggle/multiple-item switches, while others are standard
string gadgets. While in a string gadget, you can use these CONTROL keys to
help in editing:

    CONTROL - X : Will DELETE everything in the gadget.

    CONTROL - N : Will move the cursor to the END of typed input.

    CONTROL - B : Will move the cursor to the BEGINNING of typed input.

    CONTROL - K : Will DELETE everything to the RIGHT of the cursor.

    To switch to the opposite config screen, you can alternately press your
"@{" V " link VIEW}" key, instead of highlighting the VIEW MORE button.
@endnode
@Node HARDLY "Yeah, right!"

    Hardly, there's a bunch more options. Press "C" for the "Contents",
then press either the "1" on your Numeric Keypad or use the keystroke
combination of "ALT-<DOWN ARROW>" to check out the rest of the options!
@endnode
